Description: Fix 64-bit portability issues
 - main.c fixrgba(): cast unsigned char to unsigned before left-shifting by 24
   to avoid signed integer overflow (undefined behaviour) that compilers may
   misoptimise on 64-bit targets (arm64, riscv64).
 - main.c: cast fread() return value (size_t) to int before storing in int
   variable, and use (size_t) cast for sizeof comparison.
 - png_wrap.c: use unsigned int for the row loop counter to match
   png_uint_32, and cast fread()/png_uint_32 assignments explicitly.
 - overlay.c: use Uint32 for prevticks to match SDL_GetTicks(), and cast
   signed OVERLAY fields to unsigned int before comparing with the unsigned
   return of mzx_position().
